    "reasoning": "The problem requires finding the probability that exactly k games are played in a best-of-9 series, where k = n + 5 and n is the cardinality of set A admitting a consistent 2-configuration of order 1 with exactly 1 cell. A consistent 2-configuration with exactly 1 cell (a single pair) implies the set A has 2 elements (n = 2), so k = 2 + 5 = 7. For a best-of-9 series where the first team to 5 wins wins the series, exactly 7 games are played if one team wins the 7th game and has exactly 4 wins in the first 6 games. The Mathletes (probability 2/3 per game) contribute C(6,4)*(2/3)^5*(1/3)^2, and the other team contributes C(6,2)*(2/3)^2*(1/3)^5. Summing these gives 15*(32 + 4)/3^7 = 540/2187 = 20/81.",
